I2C SVT UVM Documentation - Sequence Page

svt_sequence class inheritance diagram.

Sequences defined in I2C SVT UVM Documentation:

Sequence Group Sequence Subgroup Sequences Sequences Description Controls Sequencer
SLAVE_PRIMITIVE_SEQUENCES
* This group contains all primitive level sequences.
SLV_NACK_ADDR
svt_i2c_slave_nack_addr_sequence This sequence configure Slave to send NACK for address, with User define nack_addr_count, which shows how many times slave will send NACK for it's address.

Body of the sequence executes following set of commands

  • Declares its local attributes

  • Receives the values of attributes of class from config db and if the values are not set through config db, then
    it takes randomized value.

  • Assigns received value of class attributes to its local attributes

  • Execute sequence to configure Slave for NACK for a particular data byte
 nack_addr_count
nack address count

svt_i2c_slave_transaction_sequencer
SLV_RANDOM_TRANSACTION
svt_i2c_slave_random_sequence This sequence configure Slave to send NACK for address, with User define nack_addr_count, which shows how many times slave will send NACK for it's address.

Body of the sequence executes following set of commands

  • Declares its local attributes

  • Receives the values of attributes of class from config db and if the values are not set through config db, then
    it takes randomized value.

  • Assigns received value of class attributes to its local attributes

  • Execute sequence to configure Slave for NACK for a particular data byte
 sequence_length
Parameter that controls the number of I2C frames that would be generated

svt_i2c_slave_transaction_sequencer
SLV_DATA_BIT_STRETCHING
svt_i2c_slave_data_bit_stretching_sequence This sequence configure Slave for stretching the clock after each bit of data byte, by making SCL line LOW with User define clk_stretch_time_data_byte, which shows time for which the SCL line goes LOW.

Body of the sequence executes following set of commands

  • Declares its local attributes

  • Receives the values of attributes of class from config db and if the values are not set through config db, then
    it takes default value.

  • Assigns received value of class attributes to its local attributes

  • Execute sequence to configure Slave for stretching the clock after each bit of data byte
 -- svt_i2c_slave_transaction_sequencer
SLV_ADDR_BIT_STRETCHING
svt_i2c_slave_addr_bit_stretching_sequence This sequence configure Slave for stretching the clock after each bit of Address byte, by making SCL line LOW with User define clk_stretch_time_addr_byte, which shows time for which the SCL line goes LOW.

Body of the sequence executes following set of commands

  • Declares its local attributes

  • Receives the values of attributes of class from config db and if the values are not set through config db, then
    it takes default value.

  • Assigns received value of class attributes to its local attributes

  • Execute sequence to configure Slave for stretching the clock after each bit of address byte
 -- svt_i2c_slave_transaction_sequencer
SLV_BYTE_STRETCHING
svt_i2c_slave_byte_stretching_sequence This sequence configure Slave for stretching the clock after each byte, by making SCL line LOW with User define clk_stretch_time_after_byte, which shows time for which the SCL line goes LOW.

Body of the sequence executes following set of commands

  • Declares its local attributes

  • Receives the values of attributes of class from config db and if the values are not set through config db, then
    it takes default value.

  • Assigns received value of class attributes to its local attributes

  • Execute sequence to configure Slave for stretching the clock after each byte
 -- svt_i2c_slave_transaction_sequencer
SLV_NACK_DATA
svt_i2c_slave_nack_data_sequence This sequence configure Slave for NACK for a particular data byte, with User define nack_data.

Body of the sequence executes following set of commands

  • Declares its local attributes

  • Receives the values of attributes of class from config db and if the values are not set through config db, then
    it takes default value.

  • Assigns received value of class attributes to its local attributes

  • Execute sequence to configure Slave for NACK for a particular data byte

MASTER_COMPLEX_SEQUENCES_OF_SINGLE_TYPE
* This group contains all complex level sequences
MST_RD_7BIT_SR_RD_7BIT_RANDDATA
* .
 svt_i2c_master_rd_7bit_sr_rd_7bit_randdata_sequence This sequence creates a scenario as following :
1. Read command,7-bit addressing, repeated start condition, random data with User defined data size followed by
2. Read command,7-bit addressing, user defined repeated start/stop condition, random data with User defined data size

Body of the sequence executes as follows

  • Create handles of primitive level sequences

  • Declares its local attributes

  • Receives the values of attributes of class from config db and if the values are not set through config db, then
    it takes randomized values.

  • Assigns received value of class attributes to its local attributes

  • Execute two primitive sequences to generate packets with configured address,data_size and sr_or_p_gen for both sequnces.

default -- svt_gpio_base_sequence Description-Unavailable -- svt_gpio_sequencer
svt_i2c_master_transaction_base_sequence This sequence raises/drops objections in the pre/post_body so that root sequences raise objections but subsequences do not. -- svt_i2c_master_transaction_sequencer
svt_i2c_slave_transaction_base_sequence This sequence raises/drops objections in the pre/post_body so that root sequences raise objections but subsequences do not. -- svt_i2c_slave_transaction_sequencer
